description: A pilot. A fireman. An astronaut. These are some of the things that kids wish to be when they grow up. For Joey, it is his favorite fictional superhero, Awesome Man. In admiring his strength and power, Joey lives and breathes all things Awesome Man, and daydreams about his adventures constantly. Then one evening, Joey's childhood changes forever when his pretend world becomes reality, and his fantasies unexpectedly come true. Astonish Comics invites you to come join us for the beginning of an "awesome" adventure with the new full color, all ages book from the team of writer David Oshima and creator Joe Mateo. Â

Horrid creatures are on the loose, the world seems doomed to chaos until bubbly high-school figure skater Hizuru Oborozuki and music prodigy Takuya Hijou join the fight. Descendants of a great savior, Takuya uses his music to transform Hizura into a beautiful warrior. Now the world has a fighting chance!
name: Vol. 1

description: Feeling responsible for what happened to Ichigo, Hizuru is reluctant to transform again, not wanting anyone else to get hurt. Meanwhile, Coach Minamida is betrayed by the man she loves when he gets engaged to someone else. Hizuru is forced back into action when Suspicion feeds off of Coach Minamida's feelings of loneliness and betrayal, endangering Coach Minamida-sensei as well as the rest of the world.
name: Vol. 2

description:
From Gold Key to DC! But one thing's still the same - that boy's up to his loincloth in trouble!

And he's not alone - Carson Napier returns to comics after more than a decade, and Abner Perry is introduced to comicdom, and to Pellucidar!
name: The Treasure Vaults of Opar

description: A signal picked up from Babylon 4 leads the crew to investigate, and their trek leads to no less than the testament of Valen, a Minbari not born of Minbari, in "In Valen's Name." Â
name: Book One

description: The testament of Valen continues, while Garibaldi and Sheridan try to find a way off the station that's spiralling down towards its (and their) doom in "In Valen's Name - Book Two." Â
name: Book Two

description: The Tak'cha attack, even as the connection between Valen and the Tak'cha is revealed through the history log in "In Valen's Name - Book Three." Â
name: Book Three

volume.name: Back In Black: Brian Pulido Unleashed At Avatar

description:
Out of the pages of history and into one extremely sick comic book! Prepare to meet Ript and Claude, the Dinosaur Bad Boys of the Jurassic, as they thumb their noses at T. Rex, Brontosaurs, Pterodons...basically anything bigger than they are. They're rude, crude, and have vile personal habits. You've never met anything quite as bad as the Bad Eggs!

First appearance (all dinosaurs):

  • Claude
  • Ript
  • Tee Arr
  • Jumbo Johnson
  • Master Panaam
name: Sex, Lies, and Vertrbrates

description:
Featuring the dinosaur bad boys Claude & Ript.

Cameos:

  • William Shatner
name: Dinophobia

volume.name: Bad Eggs: That Dirty Yellow Mustard

description: The word is out on the streets: a reward of five million dollars to the opportunist that wastes the courier calling herself Bambi and returns her living cargo. Chainsaw-swinging psychos, gold-toothed Elvises, Derringer-packing grannies, and all the other scum in these badlands could care less whether Bambi is kidnapping this toddler she christened "Pampi" or if she's snatching him back from his captors. With a pink gun in one hand, and a leashed Pampi in the other, can antihero Bambi's huge ego and formidable gun skills hold off an army?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Nature made Ash Lynx beautiful; nurture made him a cold ruthless killer. A runaway brought up as the adopted heir and sex toy of "Papa" Dino Golzine, Ash, now at the rebellious age of seventeen, forsakes the kingdom held out by the devil who raised him. But the hideous secret that drove Ash's older brother mad in Vietnam has suddenly fallen into Papa's insatiably ambitious hands--and it's exactly the wrong time for Eiji Okamura, a pure-hearted young photographer from Japan, to make Ash Lynx's acquaintance...

Epic in scope, and one of the best-selling shojo titles of all time in Japan, Akimi Yoshida put an electric shock into the genre and gained a huge crossover audience through Banana Fish's stripped-down, non-stop style.
name: Vol. 1

description: After a near-death experience, Claude swears off meat-eating forever. To Ript's disgust, he joins a cult of simple-minded herbivores and becomes what he eats! Poking fun at life, its foibles and the comic industry all in one fell swoop in this latest installment of Ript and Claude's black-humored adventures set in Jurassic times.
name: Vegesaurus Wrecks

description: Ript and Claude, the stars of this title are two ignorant, belly-scratching, lazy, disrespecting reptiles with no manners, no culture, no socially redeeming value whatsoever...so who better than them to instruct the granddaddy ancestor of us all -- the world's first proto-human? Being mentors to the human race is no picnic, of course, and to our two heroes, this little mammal is one big pain in their sphincters.
name: Brain Sighs

description: "The Volcano's coming, the Volcano's coming!", echo the words from Ript and Claude this issue, as Panaam collects his debt from our primordial heroes and forces them to spread the word to evacuate the jungle inhabitants to safety. But the rub, as they say, is that due to Ript and Claude's past behavior, everybody thinks they're trying to scam them. Jeez, and you thought Chicken Little had it bad.
name: Exit-Us

description:
Featuring the dinosaur bad boys Claude & Ript and a bunch of aliens.

Cameos:

  • Alf
  • The Alien
  • Chewbacca
  • E.T.
  • Jabba the Hutt
  • Marvin the Martian
  • Yoda
name: Quack! Quack! When You Whiz Upon A Star...

volume.name: Bad Eggs: That Dirty Yellow Mustard

description:
Featuring the dinosaur bad boys Claude & Ript, and Ivar Anni-Padda.

Cameos:

  • Fabian "Fabio" Nicieza
  • Turok (supposedly)
name: Much Do-Do About Nothing

volume.name: Bad Eggs: That Dirty Yellow Mustard

description: Determined to steal back Pampi, Bambi goes head-on with a battalion of gangsters who have taken over an old west-style town and are using it as a hideout while they terrorize the locals for fun. To get Pampi back, our anti-heroine will have to mow them all down, including the seemingly invincible gang leader Mama. Bambi will also have to deal with psychos in bear costumes, trucker gangs trying to capture her, a 100-year old psychotic ex-wrestler, and more!
name: Vol. 2

description: When Dino arranges Ash's frame-up for the murder of a man he had motive to kill twenty times over, an "accident" behind bars is on the agenda. But in the same prison is Max Lobo, a journalist himself on the trail of the enigma code-named Banana Fish...
name: Vol. 2

description: After a failed attempt to kill Golzine, Ash is on the lam with his friends: Shorter, a Chinese gang-member; Eiji, a Japanese reporter who is developing feelings for Ash; Eiji's boss IbÃ©; and Max Lobo, a journalist and Griffins's former army buddy. Ash heads for his childhood home in Cape Cod and a tragic meeting with his real father. Meanwhile, the group learns that Griffin knew his killer--one Abraham Dawson--back in Vietnam. Could Dawson hold the secret of Banana Fish?
name: Vol. 4

description: In search of more information about the substance, Ash flees to Los Angeles with a band of allies, where he clashes with Yau-Si, an alluring and duplicitous young assassin. Drawn in by Yau-Si, one of Ash's so-called allies betrays him to the Chinese mafia. Once again Ash is handed over to the rapacious Dino Golzine, who will do anything to cash in on Banana Fish!
name: Vol. 5

description: Eiji Okamura, a young photographer from Japan, has made Ash's acquaintance; just in time to fall with him into this bloody whirlpool. Now the Chinese Lee syndicate has delivered Ash, Max Lobo, IbÃ© and Dr. Alexis Dawson to Papa Dino. Banana Fish has been used to brainwash Shorter Wong and manipulate him into mutilating Eiji right before Ash's very eyes!
name: Vol. 6

description: Ash has only one hand of cards--a loyal posse of street thugs, an investigative reporter, and a sympathetic cop, as he plays his one draw with tricks, trumps, and the hand jive from a .357 Magnum...
name: Vol. 7

description: Ash squares off with Arthur in a final showdown, but can Arthur be trusted to stick to the rules that he has set up? This showdown has Ash and Arthur surf a sea of blood through the bowels of the New York subway system.
name: Vol. 8

description:
The epic battle between Ash and Arthur reaches its gruesome conclusion. Ash is left hospitalized, but not out of reach from the sinister hands of Papa Dino. Unbeknownst to Ash's crew, Dino has arranged Ash's transfer to a medical facility with a very special purpose in mind. Yut-Lung has finally begun to unveil his plans, but mystery still surrounds him.

Epic in scope, and one of the best-selling shÃ´jo titles of all time in Japan, Akimi Yoshida put an electric shock into the genre and gained a huge crossover audience through Banana Fish's stripped-down, non-stop style.
name: Vol. 9

description: The announcement of Ash's death on television news has young Eiji in shock and denial. Ash's body is prepared for autopsy, but Max Lobo is convinced that the body has only been made to look like Ash. Meanwhile, the real Ash Lynx is transferred to a medical compound controlled by the Union Corse and corrupt Senator Kippard, where he will be a guinea pig for the dreaded Banana Fish. But neither Ash nor his friends are content to let him rot there, and they begin their own independent escape plans!
name: Vol. 10

description: Ash and Dr. Alexis Dawson, the surviving brother of the duo that created Banana Fish, struggle to escape the mental institution where they have been committed against their will. Unbeknownst to Ash, Max and IbÃ© are also attempting to free him. Ash litters the complex's sterile hallways with the corpses of the guards who try to stop him. Then Blanc, a mysterious new character with a link to Ash's past, emerges, and Dino hires him to get Ash.
name: Vol. 11

description: Ash has finally escaped from the mental institution where he was held captive and has brought with him crucial evidence of the proof and power of the drug known as Banana Fish. Golzine has hired Blanc, the man responsible for Ash's training in the fighting arts, to bring Ash "home" at any cost!
name: Vol. 12

description: In a desperate attempt to save Eiji, Ash accepts the role of Papa Dino's right-hand man. He then threatens Max at gunpoint to give him the magazine story on Banana Fish before it hits the press. Grooming Ash to become his successor, Dino sets in motion a chain of events that will truly make him part of the "Family."
name: Vol. 13

description: Ash, freed from the clutches of Dino, races to find Eiji, but Dino's men beat him to the punch. A deadly battle rages at the National History Museum, and Ash captures Yut-Lung. Perhaps a deal can be struck and hostages exchanged...
name: Vol. 15

description: Ash and his crew are faced with a new deadly enemy, as Golzine has hired ex-member of the French Foreign Legion Colonel Fox and his elite cadre to destroy them. To fight back, Ash has formed alliances with local Chinese and African-American gangs. While the two sides clash in an all-out melee in New York's garbage-strewn back alleys and abandoned buildings, Yau-Si is still obsessed with the notion of killing Eiji...
name: Vol. 16

description:
Badger is invited to Black Lotor Liu Hu martial arts tournament held every hundred years. The prize, anything the winner desires! The loser, death!

Badger meets Mavis, a vietnamese vetenarian, along the way and together they travel to the tournament. But something is trying to stop them from getting there and winning.
Banana Man overcame his self-doubt by besting Gorilla Guy who was trying to take over the school assembly. While Banana Man was basking in his glory, Gorilla Guy was able to make his escape....
name: "Banana Blues"

description: Classic reprints of fantasy/s-f/s&s stories from the 1950's!! Wally Wood's Captain Science in "The Insidious Doctor Khartoum"; John Giunta's Crom, The Barbarian in "The Giant From Beyond"; Sid Greene's "The Flame Goddess"; and "Princess of the Past" by Larsen. Vintage full-story reprints originally published by Avon Pubs. and others...

After being bested by Banana Man, Gorilla Guy is forced to retreat. Banana Man is able to track him down at the local comic convention only to be gorilla pressed by Gorilla Guy. He also learns that Gorilla Guy works at his school...
name: "Gorilla Press"

description: Banana Man, in his ongoing effort to track down Gorilla Guy, bribes a high school football player that is running the school raffle. He is unsuccessful in discovering Gorilla Guy's identity, but he was able to lure him out into the open...
name: "Defective Comics"

description: The brawl between Banana Man and Gorilla guy on the football field gives the opportunity for Banana Man to find out who Gorilla Guy is once and for all
name: The Man of Peel

description: Banana Man is on the case for capturing a new villain named the Tinkler! You probably don't want to know why he has that name
name: Tinkle Me This

description: Banana Man wonders whether he gets through to his students about the importance of nutrition.
name: A Life in the day

description: Banana Man is back for a new assembly but it seems like Yo-Yo man wants to interrupt and talk about the importance of recreation in studentsâ lives. Yo-Yo Man captures Banana Man but Gorilla Guy comes to save him!
name: Going Bananas

description: Basara is a post-apocalyptic fantasy adventure series and one of the most popular shÃ´jo manga of the 90s in Japan. It is the story of how a young girl becomes "the child of destiny" and finds the stgrength to free her people and seek revenge for the death of her brother.
name: Vol. 1

description: After losing her family, village and identity in one night, Sarasa deserves a break, but fate denies her rest. As Tatara, she must lead her people, and the Red King has captured some of them, destined for slave labor in the capital of Kyoto. When Sarasa's impatient desire for revenge against the Red King spoils the rescue attempt, she loses more loved ones. After this terrible lesson, Sarasa is unable to continue risking the lives of those who are dear to her. Alone, she heads to Kyushu in search of allies, but to get to Kyushu, she must first pass through Suo City, capital of the Red King's domain!
name: Lessons In Leadership

description: Accepting the identity and responsibility of the "Boy of Destiny" following her brother's death, Sarasa has left her people in safety, traveling alone to Kyushu in search of allies. After surviving great perils and gaining a new companion, Sarasa arrives at her destination only to discover it's no longer there!
name: Vol. 3

description: Secretly taking her late brother's identity, Sarasa must gain support as the "Boy of Destiny." Her courage and quick wits have turned the pirates who captured her into allies and an impossible situation into victory. Now she must survive an erupting volcano and a tenacious enemy.
name: Vol. 4
